        <p id="titleJoke"></p>
    </header>
    
    <p>This is a Programming Jokes REST API created with node.js and express.<br> It implements all of the most common features a REST API has: GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE.<br> Some of the requests require basic HTTP authentication, which requires a registration or an API KEY assigned to each user.</p>
    <h2>GET /random</h2>
    <p>Outputs a random joke. No authentication is required.</p>
    <p>Sample request:</p>
    <p class="snippet"><span class="green">GET</span> https:/API_URL.com/random</p>
    <p>Sample response:</p>
    <p class="snippet">{<br>"id":11,<br>"type":"General",<br>"joke":"Why don't programmers like to go outside? The sunlight causes too many glares on their screens."<br>}</p>
    
    <a></a>
    <h2>GET /id/:id</h2>
    <p>Outputs the joke with the requested id. The first joke has id of 1. Basic Authentication or an API key is required.</p>
    <p>Sample request:</p>
    <p class="snippet"><span class="green">GET</span> https:/user:password@API_URL.com/id/5</p>
    <p class="snippet"><span class="green">GET</span> https:/API_URL.com/id/5?apiKey=abcdef123456</p>
    <p>Sample response:</p>
    <p class="snippet">{<br>"id":5,<br>"type":"HTML",<br>"joke":"How do you cheer up a web developer? You console them."<br>}</p>
    <h2>GET /filter?type=TYPE</h2>
    <p>Outputs all the jokes that belong to TYPE. The available types are: "general", "Python", "JavaScript", "Cpp", "HTML", "SQL", "Java", "Swift". Basic Authentication or an API key is required.</p>
    <p>Sample request:</p>
    <p class="snippet"><span class="green">GET</span> https:/user:password@API_URL.com/filter?type=SQL</p>
    <p class="snippet"><span class="green">GET</span> https:/API_URL.com/filter?type=SQL&apiKey=abcdef123456</p>
    <p>Sample response:</p>
    <p class="snippet">[<br>
        {<br>
          "id": 7,<br>
          "type": "SQL",<br>
          "joke": "Why do SQL developers hate the sea? Because it’s full of JOINs."<br>
        },<br>
        {<br>
          "id": 17,<br>
          "type": "SQL",<br>
          "joke": "Why do SQL developers have trouble with relationships? They can't handle too many joins."<br>
        },<br>
        {<br>
          "id": 40,<br>
          "type": "SQL",<br>
          "joke": "Why did the SQL query feel so powerful? It was able to join all the tables."<br>
        }<br>
      ]</p>
    <h2>GET /all</h2>
    <p>Outputs all the jokes. Basic Authentication or an API key is required.</p>
    <p>Sample request:</p>
    <p class="snippet"><span class="green">GET</span> https:/user:password@API_URL.com/all</p>
    <p class="snippet"><span class="green">GET</span> https:/API_URL.com/all?apiKey=abcdef123456</p>
    <p>Sample response:</p>
    <p class="snippet">[<br>
